Active experiments refer to the ones that are currently in progress or have not been completed; 
Active models are those that are being used or considered in the experiments;
Performance metrics include the R-squared value (r2), which measures the goodness of fit of the model, the size of the training dataset (train_set_size), and the size of the test dataset (test_set_size).

- 'Top-performing' in the context of models refers to those with the best evaluation metrics, implying a balance between high R-squared values (closer to 1) and low error metrics (RMSE and MAE closer to 0); 
- R-squared (R2) measures how well the model explains the variance in the target variable;
- Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) calculates the square root of the mean of squared errors, providing a measure of how spread out these errors are.

